Package eecs.jago.element

Provides the individual elements for the simulation.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Attachment This interface describes elements that are attached to other elements.
Collidable A Collidable element will interact with other Collidable elements during a collision.
Destructible This interface describes any object that can be destroyed during the course of the simulation.
FlatObject An empty interface that identifies objects that can be driven over.
LightSource Interface to create a light source in the simulation.
Mobile An interface that can be used to provide SimElements the ability to move around the simulation.
Monitor An object that can monitor sensors.
Propulsion An interface for elements that have the ability to move.
Pushable An empty interface that can be used to determine if objects can be pushed.
Reflective A Reflective object will appear to reflect lighting.
ReflectiveColors The colors that can be detected using a reflectance sensitive sensor.
RobotSensors The types of sensors that can be attached to a StandardRobot.
RobotState This interface contains no functionality; it is used only to maintain the robot state constants.
SensorState The SensorState interface maintains the standard states of robot sensors.
Visible A Visible object has the ability to display itself if given a context to draw in.
